('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '64289b52-861b-4a49-9286-4c4196691af7', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Identify the INCORRECT method for reclamation of uncultivable agriculture land due to waterlogging and salinity.', 'Leaching', 'Application of 1 to 5 percent solution of sodium chloride chemical', 'Adopting rice cultivation', 'Drainage and lowering of water table', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '64289b52-861b-4a49-9286-4c4196691af7', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Which of the following does represent the irrigating capacity of a unit quantity of water?', 'Base Period', 'Field Capacity', 'Delta', 'Duty', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '64289b52-861b-4a49-9286-4c4196691af7', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'A crop requires a total depth of 100 cm of water for a base period of 200 days, determine the duty of irrigating water.', '17.28 hectares/cumec', '14.32 hectares/cumec', '1728 hectares/cumec', '1432 hectares/cumec', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '64289b52-861b-4a49-9286-4c4196691af7', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Which of the following is/are the correct remedies to prevent the rupture of weir floor due to suction caused by standing wave? Statements: 1. Providing additional thickness of floor to counterbalance the extra pressure due to the standing wave. 2. Constructing the floor thickness in one concrete mass instead of masonry layers.', 'Both statements are correct.', 'Statement 1 is incorrect and statement 2 is correct.', 'Both statements are incorrect.', 'Statement 2 is incorrect and statement 1 is correct.', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '64289b52-861b-4a49-9286-4c4196691af7', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Which of the following is/are the disadvantage(s) of Tipping Bucket Rain Gauge? Statements: 1. The Tipping Bucket Rain Gauge is most suitable for measuring snow. 2. The Tipping Bucket Rain Gauge does not give accurate results in the case of intense rainfall because some of the rain, which falls during the period when the bucket is emptying, is not measured. 3. The record consists of a series of steps and not a conventional smooth mass curve required for precipitation analysis.', 'Only 1', 'Only 2', 'Only 3', '2 and 3 only', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '64289b52-861b-4a49-9286-4c4196691af7', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Arrange the following steps for design of flood control project in the correct chronological order (from the earliest to the latest). A. Select the flood control measure or a combination of measures which offers the desired protection at a minimum cost. B. Perform the economic analysis of the benefits and costs to determine whether the selected project is economical viable. C. Estimate the project design flood and determine the flood characteristics of the given area. D. Design the flood control works for different alternatives of flood control measures so that the cost estimates may be made and their effects on the flood discharge may be estimated.', 'A, B, C, D', 'C, D, A, B', 'D, C, A, B', 'B, A, C, D', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '64289b52-861b-4a49-9286-4c4196691af7', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Match the items under List 1 (Basis of Classification of Canal) with those under List 2 (Type/Name of Canal) in Classification of Canals and choose the correct option. P. Canal Alignment Q. Functions of the canal R. Discharge & its relative importance S. Boundary surface of the canal', 'P-4,Q-1,R-2,S-3', 'P-2,Q-4,R-1,S-3', 'P-3,Q-1,R-4,S-2', 'P-4,Q-3,R-1,S-2', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'According to IS 10500: 2012, in absence of an alternate source, how much is the maximum permissible limit of ''colour'', for drinking water, provided that toxic substances are not suspected in the available water source?', '5 Hazen units', '5 NTU units', '15 NTU units', '15 Hazen units', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Which of the following is the correct formula to estimate the annual volume (cum) required for a landfill? {where, P = Population, m = average mass(kg) of solid waste collected per person per year, V = annual volume, p = compacted fill density (kg/m³)}', 'Pm/p', 'Pmp', 'P', '', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Read the following statements regarding drinking water parameters and choose the correct option. Statements: 1. When protection against viral infection is required, concentration of free residual chlorine should be minimum 0.5mg/l in the drinking water. 2. The maximum limit of Sulphate (as SO₄) may be extended (in absence of alternate source) to 400 mg/l, only if the Magnesium does not exceed 30mg/l, in the drinking water.', 'Both statements are incorrect.', 'Statement 1 is correct and statement 2 is incorrect.', 'Both statements are correct.', 'Statement 1 is incorrect and statement 2 is correct.', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Arrange the following Air Pollution Control Devices in their increasing order of efficiency. A. Fabric Filter B. Electrostatic Precipitator C. Wet Scrubber D. Gravitational Settling Chamber', 'B, D, C, A', 'C, A, D, B', 'A, B, C, D', 'D, C, B, A', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'For areas of moderate sizes, such as involved for branch sewers, the maximum daily sewage flows can be expressed as', '2 X average daily flow', '4 X average daily flow', '0.5 X average daily flow', '6 X average daily flow', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Choose the most appropriate range of the ratio of ultimate BOD (Bio- chemical oxygen demand) to the COD (Chemical Oxygen Demand) of a waste water, so that it may be considered as fully biodegradable.', '1.2 to 1.5', '0.9 to 1.0', '0.1 to 0.2', '2.2 to 2.5', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The upper layer of lake water through which sunlight can penetrate is known as:', 'Euphotic Zone', 'Littoral Zone', 'Benthic Zone', 'Oligotrophic Zone', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Calculate the BOD₅ (kg/day) of the waste water of an industry, if the population equivalent of the industrial waste water is 3750 and average standard BOD₅ of domestic sewage is 0.08 kg/day/person.', '5000', '46875', '300', '480', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Which of the following is/are the disadvantage(s) of interceptor related to house drainage in buildings? 1. Cleaning through the inspection arm of the interceptor trap is not easy. 2. Foul gases of the public sewer cannot pass through the interceptor. 3. Interceptor itself forms an obstruction to the normal flow of sewage.', 'Only 1', 'Only 2', 'Only 3', '1 and 3 only', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Which of the following is the incorrectly matched pair of material of sewer and its non- scouring velocity (cm/sec)?', 'Ordinary Brick-Lined Sewers - 150 to 250', 'Cement Concrete Sewers - 250 to 300', 'Cast Iron Sewer Pipes - 60 to 120', 'Vitrified Tile - 450 to 500', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The forces whose lines of action do not lie in one plane and they do not meet at one point are known as', 'Non- coplanar and Non- concurrent forces', 'Non- coplanar and concurrent forces', 'Coplanar and Non- concurrent forces', 'Coplanar and concurrent forces', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The resultant of two concurrent coplanar forces P & Q is R. If the direction of force Q is reversed then resultant of the forces become S, then (R² + S²) will be equal to ______.', '(P² + Q²)²', '4(P²+Q²)', '2(P²- Q²)', '2(P²+Q²)', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Read the following statements regarding equilibrium of coplanar and concurrent forces and choose the correct option. Statements: 1. If two forces acting on a body are represented in magnitude and direction by the two sides of a triangle taken in order, then their resultant is given by the third side of the triangle taken in the opposite order. 2. If three forces acting on a particle keep it in equilibrium, then each force is proportional to the cosine of the angle between the other two forces.', 'Both statements are incorrect.', 'Statement 1 is correct and statement 2 is incorrect.', 'Both statements are correct.', 'Statement 1 is incorrect and statement 2 is correct.', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Find the incorrectly matched pair of moment of inertia and its formula related to the given rectangular lamina.', 'I_y'' - (db³)/3', 'I_x - (bd³)/12', 'I_y - (db³)/12', 'I_x'' - (bd³)/2', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'A steel flat 150mm wide and 20mm thick is subjected to a tensile stress of 200N/mm². Find the strain induced in the steel flat. (Take Young''s modulus of elasticity = 2×10⁵ N/mm²)', '0.01', '0.001', '0.150', '0.00075', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'A cantilever beam of a 2m span has a left end A as a free end, whereas the right end B is the fixed supported end. It is acted upon by a point load of 10kN at the free end. The maximum bending moment will occur at', 'point A''', 'the midpoint of the span', '0.5m from point A''', 'point B''', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'aee3c24f-8b41-461f-8e64-e9544a04c1b6', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Following IS 1200, match the items under List 1 (Type of work) with those under List 2 (nearest decimal value of measurement). Use codes in lists for matching. P) Length dimension in earthwork (in m units) Q) Length dimension in earthwork done by mechanical means, when dimension is more than 25 m (in m units). R) Thickness of slab in concrete works (in m units). S) Area of steel work (in m² units)', 'P-3,Q-4,R-2,S-1', 'P-2,Q-3,R-1,S-4', 'P-4,Q-1,R-2,S-3', 'P-2,Q-1,R-4,S-3', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Arrange the following points on stress - strain curve of tension test in chronological order (from the earliest to the latest) of their appearance. A. Fracture Point B. Yield Point C. Proportional Limit D. Elastic Limit', 'D, B, A, C', 'C, D, B, A', 'A, C, D, B', 'B, A, C, D', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Which of the following statements regarding Euler''s Assumptions is/are correct? Statements: 1. The length of column is very large as compared to cross- sectional dimensions. 2. The cross- section of the column is uniform throughout its length.', 'Both statements are incorrect.', 'Statement 1 is correct and statement 2 is incorrect.', 'Both statements are correct.', 'Statement 1 is incorrect and statement 2 is correct.', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Match the items under List 1 (Type of Beam & Loading Conditions) with those under List 2 (Value of maximum deflection) and choose the correct option. P. Cantilever Beam of span L subjected to point load "P" at free end. Q. Cantilever Beam of span L subjected to uniformly distributed load of intensity "p" per unit length on entire span R. Simply Supported beam of span L subjected to point load "P" at mid span S. Simply Supported beam of span L subjected to uniformly distributed load of intensity "p" per unit length on entire span', 'P-4,Q-1,R-2,S-3', 'P-2,Q-4,R-1,S-3', 'P-3,Q-1,R-4,S-2', 'P-4,Q-3,R-1,S-2', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '3f275622-18e3-40ce-a134-ec660b48190c', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The scale of a map is represented as 1 : 50000. The distance between two points A and B is measured as 10 cm in the map. The actual distance between the two points in the field is:', '0.5 km', '5 km', '50 km', '500 m', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '3f275622-18e3-40ce-a134-ec660b48190c', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Consider the electromagnetic spectrum used in remote sensing. Match the items under List 1 (Wave length values) with those under List 2 (Name of region in electromagnetic spectrum). P. 0.4 to 0.7 μm Q. 0.7 to 3 μm R. 3 to 14 μm S. 1mm to 1m', 'P-3,Q-1,R-4,S-2', 'P-2,Q-3,R-4,S-1', 'P-4,Q-1,R-2,S-3', 'P-4,Q-3,R-1,S-2', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '3f275622-18e3-40ce-a134-ec660b48190c', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Consider the following statements based on stadia tacheometry: P. Stadia tacheometry is based on readings taken against the stadia cross hairs and two forms of stadia method (fixed hair and movable hair) are used. Q. Fixed hair stadia method uses a special diaphragm that enable to change the distance between the cross hairs, the intercept is kept constant even though the distance varies. R. Movable hair method, wherein the distance between the stadia hairs is kept constant, the intercept varies as the distance varies. Identify the correct statements and choose the correct option.', 'P only', 'Q only', 'Q and R only', 'P, Q, and R', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '3f275622-18e3-40ce-a134-ec660b48190c', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The bearings to four stations taken using a prismatic compass are given below in Table. Covert them into reduced bearings and arrange the points in the increasing order of magnitude of reduced bearing values. Point P:275°30'', Q:165°30'', R:192°00'', S:328°30''', 'Q, R, S, P', 'R, Q, S, P', 'S, R, P, Q', 'P, Q, S, R', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '3f275622-18e3-40ce-a134-ec660b48190c', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Among the different corrections applied to a chain surveying identify the correction which is not always negative.', 'Correction due to wrong alignment', 'Correction due to slope', 'Correction due to pull', 'Correction due to sag', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '3f275622-18e3-40ce-a134-ec660b48190c', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'In a total station survey work, the leveling of the total station and exact centering at a station are respectively done by using:', 'Optical plummet and Automatic compensator', 'Tripod legs and Standards (A- frame)', 'Optical plummet, tripod legs and circular bubble', 'Tripod legs, Levelling Foot screws and Optical plummet', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'a3efd61d-542a-4076-8ffe-631b227f0239', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Arrange the operations involved in the manufacture of burnt clay bricks in the chronological order (first to last operation). Use codes for answering. W - Weathering; D - Digging; T - Tempering; B - Blending; M - Moulding; U - Unsolling; DR - Drying; BU - Burning', 'U - W - D - T - B - M - DR - BU', 'D - U - W - T - B - M - DR - BU', 'D - W - U - T - B - DR - M - BU', 'U - D - W - B - T - M - DR - BU', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'a3efd61d-542a-4076-8ffe-631b227f0239', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'According to IS : 1237 - 1980, the average wet transverse strength of cement concrete flooring tiles shall not be less than', '3 N/mm²', '5 N/mm²', '10 N/mm²', '7.5 N/mm²', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'a3efd61d-542a-4076-8ffe-631b227f0239', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Consider the following statements based on the seasoning of timber. P. Seasoning is the process of reducing the moisture content of timber in order to prevent the timber from possible fermentation and making it suitable for use. Q. Foxiness, upsets, rind galls are some of the defects caused in timber due to seasoning. R. Reduction in shrinkage, warping and reduction in weight of timber occurs due to seasoning. S. Seasoning reduces the natural defects in timber. Identify the correct statements, and choose the correct option.', 'P and S only', 'P and R only', 'Q and S only', 'P, Q, and S only', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'a3efd61d-542a-4076-8ffe-631b227f0239', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Consider the following pairs with respect to glass : P. Soda lime glass : Crown glass Q. Bullet proof glass : Fusing a mixture of silica, borax, lime and felspar R. Imparts Colour, brightness and shine to glass : Lead oxide S. Accelerator for the fusion of glass : Lime Choose the correct answer on matching.', 'P only', 'Q and S only', 'P and R only', 'Q, R, and S only', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'a3efd61d-542a-4076-8ffe-631b227f0239', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Consider the Properties of building materials. Match the items under List 1 (Properties of materials) with those under List 2 (Definition of Properties). P. Weathering resistance Q. Frost resistance R. Hygroscopicity S. Refractiveness', 'P-3,Q-4,R-1,S-2', 'P-2,Q-4,R-1,S-3', 'P-4,Q-3,R-2,S-1', 'P-2,Q-3,R-4,S-1', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'aee3c24f-8b41-461f-8e64-e9544a04c1b6', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'According to Indian standards, what is the size of opening and size of frame of a door represented as SDS20.', 'Size of opening = 800mmX2000mm ; size of frame = 790mmX1990mm', 'Size of opening = 810mmX2010mm ; size of frame = 800mmX2000mm', 'Size of opening = 800mmX2000mm ; size of frame = 780mmX1980mm', 'Size of opening = 820mmX2020mm ; size of frame = 800mmX2000mm', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'a3efd61d-542a-4076-8ffe-631b227f0239', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Following the National Building Code of India, 2016, if W is the width of supported wall (in mm units), the width at the base of wall foundation (in mm units) B, shall not be less than :', 'B = W + 200', 'B = W + 300', 'B = W + 250', 'B = W + 100', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'a3efd61d-542a-4076-8ffe-631b227f0239', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Following the national building code of india 2016, Arrange the following buildings according to the increasing order (lowest to highest) of floor area ratios for occupancies facing one public street of at least 9m width. Use codes for answering. H. Hazardous type 1 I. Industrial type 1 E. Educational type 1 M. Mercantile type 1', 'E-M-I-H', 'M-I-E-H', 'H-I-M-E', 'E-H-I-M', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements(P, Q, R, S) pertain to force system acting on bodies. P. Equal and opposite forces acting on a body always constitute a couple action on the body. Q. Coplanar force systems can be concurrent or non-concurrent, parallel or non-parallel. R. Forces may act over a line, a surface or a volume, and are correspondingly denoted as lineal, surface and body forces. S. The concept of moment of a force is equal to the sum of moments due to its components is not valid always. Identify the correct statements, and choose the correct option.', 'P and Q only', 'R and S only', 'Q and R only', 'P, R, S only', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Consider the centroids of the following geometric shapes. ( y_cg : distance to centroidal axis XX from the bottom or base) P. Quarter of a circle of radius R with its base parallel to the centroidal axis in X direction: y_cg = 3π/4R Q. Triangle of base b and height h with the base b parallel to centroidal axis in X direction: y_cg = h/3 R. Semi-circle of radius R with its diameter (as base) kept parallel to the centroidal axis in X direction: y_cg = 4R/3π S. Square of side a with its side kept parallel to centroidal axis in X direction: y_cg = a/2 Choose the correct answer on matching.', 'P only', 'Q and S only', 'P and R only', 'Q, R, and S only', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Three forces as shown in Figure, act at the centre O of a body, keep the body in equilibrium. Determine the magnitude of the force P in kN units?', '100 cos 130', '100 sin 130', '100 sin 140', '100 cos 140', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'A mild steel specimen is subjected to a tension test to plot its stress strain behaviour. The chronological order in which the following stress points occur during the progress of test (first to the last) is : (Use codes for answering) Y - Yield point ; E - Elastic limit ; B - Breaking stress ; U - Ultimate stress', 'Y-E-B-U', 'E-Y-U-B', 'Y-E-U-B', 'E-Y-B-U', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements (P, Q) pertain to strain energy stored in a material. P : The maximum strain energy that can be stored in a material without permanent set is when the stress σ is equal to the stress f at elastic limit of the material. Q : If f is the stress at the elastic limit of a material, then modulus of resilience = f²/E , where E is the Young''s modulus of material. Choose the correct statement(s)', 'P only', 'Q only', 'Both P and Q', 'Neither P nor Q', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The bending moment diagram of a simply supported beam AC with supports at A and C is shown in figure. The load acting on the beam is :', 'A couple applied at the point B', 'A concentrated load at the point B', 'A uniformly distributed load over the whole length of beam AC', 'Equal and Opposite moments applied at A and C', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'For a cantilever beam of span L different type of loads are applied. Match the Item List 1 (Type and position of load on a cantilever beam) with List 2 (shape of bending moment diagram) and select the correct answer using the codes given in lists : P. Carrying concentrated load at free end Q. Uniformly distributed load over entire span R. Carry a linearly varying load with zero at free end and maximum at fixed end S. Free end is subjected to a couple', 'P-4,Q-3,R-2,S-1', 'P-2,Q-3,R-4,S-1', 'P-3,Q-4,R-2,S-1', 'P-2,Q-1,R-4,S-3', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Consider application of Eulers theory for long columns. Arrange the columns for the situations given below on the basis of the increasing order of crippling load (lowest to highest values). Use codes for answering. (Note : Assume the columns in all cases have same length and EI values) P - Both ends of the column are hinged. Q - Both ends of the column are fixed. R - One end of the column is fixed and the other end is hinged. S - One end of the column is fixed and the other end is free.', 'S - R - Q - P', 'R - P - Q - S', 'S - P - R - Q', 'P - R - Q - S', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements (P, Q, R, S) pertain to the assumptions for the analysis of perfect truss. P. The joints in the truss are rigidly fixed and can resist moments. Q. The load on the truss is applied at the joints only. R. The centroidal lines of the members at a joint, meet at the joint. S. The truss can be loaded either on the joints or on the members in between joints. Identify the correct statements, and choose the correct option.', 'P, Q, R, S', 'P and S only', 'P, R and S only', 'Q ad R only', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'dd2eab18-a6c2-4636-a005-1f9ea9aef419', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements pertain to the applicability of the "middle third rule" on analysis of retaining walls subjected to direct and bending stresses. P. The rule can be applied irrespective of the shapes of the bottom section of the retaining wall. Q. This condition pertains to the development of maximum compressive stress at any point of the wall section. Choose the correct statement(s).', 'P only', 'Q only', 'Both P and Q', 'Neither P nor Q', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'a8556419-0986-4502-80b2-78b7defb8990', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'If at a point in a fluid flow system the gauge pressure reading is measured as, 200kN/m² express the pressure as absolute pressure (in metre of water units). Take atmospheric pressure as 10m of water, and unit weight of water as 10kN/m³.', '20 m', '30 m', '10 m', '12 m', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'a8556419-0986-4502-80b2-78b7defb8990', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'If P represents the fluid flow parameter at a fixed point in space, then the condition for steady flow can be stated as: (Notation : t - time ; s - space)', '∂P/∂t = 0', '∂P/∂t ≠ 0', '∂P/∂s = 0', '∂P/∂s ≠ 0', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'a8556419-0986-4502-80b2-78b7defb8990', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements (P, Q) pertain to flow through pipes. P : The hydraulic grade line and the total energy line are coincident for a body of water at rest. Q : The total energy line in a flow of an ideal fluid in a horizontal pipe with no addition of external energy will always be horizontal. Choose the correct statement(s)', 'P only', 'Q only', 'Both P and Q', 'Neither P nor Q', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'a8556419-0986-4502-80b2-78b7defb8990', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'What is the wetted perimeter of flow of the channel for the most economical section of a rectangular open channel, the hydraulic radius is 1 m.', '1 m', '2 m', '4 m', '8 m', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'a8556419-0986-4502-80b2-78b7defb8990', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Among the flow measuring devices given as options, identify the one which is used for the measurement of velocity of flow in both open channel flow and pipe flow.', 'Rectangular notch', 'Pivot tube', 'Piezometer', 'Orifice meter', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements (P,Q,R) are based on the assumptions on which the design of reinforced concrete structures is done, following the limit state of collapse. P. Stress-strain curve of concrete is assumed to follow a linear variation. Q. Maximum stress in the characteristic stress strain curve of concrete in flexural compression is restricted to 0.67 fck (where fck is characteristic compressive strength of concrete) R. The design stress strain curve is obtained by scaling down the ordinates of the characteristic stress strain curve by the appropriate partial safety factor. Identify the correct statement(s) and choose the correct option.', 'P only', 'Q only', 'Q and R only', 'P,Q,R', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements (P, Q) pertain to the working stress method of design (WSD) of reinforced concrete structures. P : WSD discriminates between different types of loads in design that act simultaneously, but have different degrees of uncertainty, through partial safety factors. Q : WSD assumes a factor of safety being the ratio of the strength of the material to the permissible stress in material. Choose the correct statement(s).', 'P only', 'Q only', 'Both P and Q', 'Neither P nor Q', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'According to IS 456: 2000, when the span is less than 3.5 m and imposed load less than 3kN/m², the span to overall depth ratio of continuous two- way RCC slabs with Fe415 steel can be taken as :', '35', '32', '36', '28', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'As per IS 456 : 2000, the value of minimum eccentricity to be adopted for the design of a reinforced concrete rectangular column of size 300 mm x 300 mm , having unsupported length of 3.3m is :', '10 mm', '6.6 mm', '16.6 mm', '20 mm', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Consider the following pairs with respect to the members of a steel roof truss : P. Principal tie : Top chord member subjected to compressive forces. Q. Sling : Main inclined members carrying tension. R. Principal rafter : Lower chord member subjected to tensile forces. S. Strut : Members under compression. Choose the correct answer on matching.', 'P and R only', 'Q and S only', 'P, R and S only', 'R only', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements (P, Q) pertain to design of steel compression members. P. The tendency of a member to buckle is usually measured by its slenderness ratio. Q. The longer the compression member becomes for the same cross section, the smaller becomes its tendency to buckle. Choose the correct statement(s).', 'P only', 'Q only', 'Both P and Q', 'Neither P nor Q', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements (P, Q, R) pertain to design of steel beam members subjected to bending. P. For a laterally unsupported beam, the design bending strength may be governed by lateral torsional buckling strength. Q. Web crippling in a steel beam occurs due to excessive bending moment. R. The design bending strength of beam adequately supported against lateral torsion buckling is governed by the yield stress. Identify the correct statement(s) and choose the correct option.', 'P only', 'Q only', 'P and R only', 'P, Q, R', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'According to IS 800:2007, the partial safety for Dead load to be adopted under Limit state of Strength criteria, with the combination of loadings taken as DL + LL + CL (DL : Dead load, LL : Live load, CL : Crane load) is :', '1.5', '1.0', '1.2', '0.9', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'According to IS 800:2007, the recommended values of the following physical properties : Unit mass (ρ), Modulus of Elasticity (E), and Poisson''s ratio (μ) of structural steel (irrespective of the grade) for use in design, are to be taken as:', 'ρ = 785kg/m³; E = 2000MPa; μ = 0.25', 'ρ = 9850kg/m³; E = 2×10⁶ MPa; μ = 0.4', 'ρ = 6850kg/m³; E = 2×10⁴ MPa; μ = 0.2', 'ρ = 7850kg/m³; E = 2×10⁵ MPa; μ = 0.3', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'A steel built up column is subjected to an axial force of 3000kN. The lacing system has to be designed for resisting a transverse shear of :', '30 kN', '45 kN', '75 kN', '150 kN', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'e7eaeaa0-d839-4490-abed-c71027b61424', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'When fillet welds are subjected to normal stress (σ) and shear stress (τ), the equivalent stress on the weld (f) is computed as :', '√(σ² + τ²)', '√(3σ² + τ²)', '√(σ² + 3τ²)', '√(0.5σ² + 3τ²)', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '64289b52-861b-4a49-9286-4c4196691af7', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'In canal irrigation, the duty of water at the head of main canal, head of distributary, head of water course and that at field are represented as DM, DD, DW, DF respectively. Arrange them in the decreasing order of duty values.', 'DM-DW-DD-DF', 'DF-DW-DD-DM', 'DF-DD-DW-DM', 'DM-DD-DW-DF', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '64289b52-861b-4a49-9286-4c4196691af7', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Consider the following pairs with respect to diversion head works in a river: P. Weir : Structure constructed across a river for heading up of water effected by gates alone. Q. Barrage : Solid obstruction constructed across a river using masonry/concrete for heading up of water. R. Divide wall : Built at right angle to the axis of weir to prevent cross currents and flow parallel to the weir S. Fish ladder : Provided parallel to the axis of weir for migration of fishes. Choose the correct answer on matching.', 'P and Q only', 'Q and S only', 'P, R and S only', 'R only', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '64289b52-861b-4a49-9286-4c4196691af7', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Due to a storm of specified magnitude and duration, direct runoff occurs from a basin. The components direct runoff due to the storm is :', 'Surface runoff, prompt interflow and channel precipitation', 'Surface runoff and channel precipitation', 'Surface runoff, delayed interflow and base flow', 'Surface runoff and infiltration', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '64289b52-861b-4a49-9286-4c4196691af7', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'In irrigation practices, which of the following in field moisture deficiency is the water required to bring the soil moisture content of the soil?', 'Saturation capacity', 'Field capacity', 'Wilting point', 'Hygroscopic capacity', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '64289b52-861b-4a49-9286-4c4196691af7', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following details pertain to the crossing of a canal and a natural drain. Bed level of Canal = +111m ; Full Supply depth of Canal = 1.8m ; Bed level of Drain = +109.4m ; depth of flow at High Flood Level = 2.2m. The suitable type of Cross drainage work is :', 'Aqueduct', 'Super Passage', 'Canal syphon', 'Syphon Aqueduct', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements (P, Q, R) pertain to the intakes / transportation of water. P. Weir intake is type of Canal intake. Q. Pipe intake is a type of River intake R. Gravity conduits for water conveyance are designed in such a way that it follows the natural hydraulic gradient. Identify the correct statements and choose the correct option.', 'P and Q only', 'Q and R only', 'P and R only', 'R only', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The water treatment proposed for the township of an industry consists of the following unit operations. P. Post chlorination Q. Demineralization R. Rapid sand filtration S. Softening Arrange the treatment units in the chronological order. Use codes.', 'P-R-Q-S', 'R-P-Q-S', 'S-R-Q-P', 'R-S-P-Q', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Which is the most acceptable economical option for solid waste management?', 'Composting', 'Pyrolysis', 'Incineration', 'Landfill', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'A conventional rapid mixing tank is treating water at 144 Million litres/day. If the hydraulic retention time is 72 second, the tank volume will be :', '72 m³', '120 m³', '100 m³', '10 m³', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements (P, Q) pertain to air pollutants. P. Secondary air pollutants are those that are produced in the air by the interaction of two or more primary air pollutants. Q. Peroxy Acetyl Nitrate (PAN) comes under the category of secondary air pollutants. Identify the correct statement(s) and choose the correct option.', 'P only', 'Q only', 'Both P and Q', 'Neither P nor Q', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Match the following items under List 1 (Purpose served by valve) with those under List 2 (Name of valve). P. To stop and regulate the flow of water under ordinary operations or emergency. Q. Situated in the line on a slope such that each section of the line between the line valves can be drained completely. R. To prevent the reversal of flow in a pipeline. S. Provided in summit of a pipeline to keep the pressure in the pipeline below a specified value.', 'P - 3, Q - 4, R - 2, S - 1', 'P - 3, Q - 2, R - 4, S - 1', 'P-2,Q-3,R-1,S-4', 'P-4,Q-3,R-2,S-1', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The treatments that are done in a conventional sewage treatment plant are listed. 1. Primary sedimentation 2. Screening 3. Trickling filter 4. Grit chamber 5. Disinfection 6. Secondary sedimentation Indicate the sequential order in which the treatments are done (use the codes).', '2-1-4-3-5-6', '4-1-2-3-6-5', '4-2-1-3-5-6', '2-4-1-3-6-5', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'From a sewage pumping station, a sample of 2.5 milli litre (ml) of raw sewage has been diluted to 250 ml and the Initial dissolved oxygen and Final dissolved oxygen of the sample are 12mg/litre, 5mg/litre respectively, what is the Biological oxygen demand (BOD) of the raw sewage.', '1200 mg/l', '700 mg/l', '240 mg/l', '500 mg/l', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'As per CPHEEO guidelines, in sewerage system design, for the estimation of per capita sewage flow, the peak factor for the contributory population is taken as :', 'Always a constant value', 'High values for high population', 'High values for low population', 'Low values for low population', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c542f294-548d-4129-8d45-b3f75629dc1b', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'For sewage treatment using an oxidation pond, when it gets overloaded, what is the chemical that is added to stimulate the algal growth.', 'Sodium nitrate', 'Sodium chloride', 'Calcium hydroxide', 'Bleaching powder', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '637bf719-8dde-4035-946c-4242372328e2', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Consider the following types of road surface in a locality where the rainfall intensity is the same. B. Thin Bituminous surface roads E. Earth roads G. Gravel roads C. Cement concrete roads The correct sequence of roads in the ascending order of steepness of camber (low to high values) of the above roads is : (Use codes for answering)', 'E - G - B - C', 'B - C - E - G', 'G - C - B - E', 'C - B - G - E', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '637bf719-8dde-4035-946c-4242372328e2', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Consider the following pairs with respect to traffic regulation in roads : P. Rotary island : Traffic control Structure . Q. Traffic studies : Traffic flow characteristics. R. Speed limit sign : Informatory sign S. Clover leaf interchange : Grade separation. Choose the correct answer on matching.', 'P and Q only', 'R and S only', 'P, Q and S only', 'R only', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '637bf719-8dde-4035-946c-4242372328e2', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements (P, Q) pertain to design of pavements . P. Westergaard''s stress equation method is used for the design of flexible pavements. Q. California bearing ratio (CBR) method is used for the design of concrete pavements. Identify the correct statement(s) and choose the correct option.', 'P only', 'Q only', 'Both P and Q', 'Neither P nor Q', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '637bf719-8dde-4035-946c-4242372328e2', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'In a horizontal circular highway curve, for a constant value of co- efficient of lateral friction, the value of required super elevation:', 'Increases with Increase in speed and decrease in radius of curve', 'Increases with decrease in both speed and radius of curve', 'Increases with Increase in both speed and radius of curve', 'Decreases with Increase in speed and decrease in radius of curve', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '637bf719-8dde-4035-946c-4242372328e2', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'In a highway an ascending gradient of 1 in 50 meets another ascending gradient of 1 in 30, determine the deviation angle?', '55', '75', '330', '', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', '637bf719-8dde-4035-946c-4242372328e2', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'As per IRC : 73 - 1980, what is the width of carriage way for non- urban highway two lane road with raised kerbs.', '7 m', '8 m', '7.5 m', '6.5 m', 3, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c39bc91d-4a88-42c6-b1f7-ae4fc2b0dba1', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements (P, Q, R, S) are given P. Consolidation is a function of total stress on soil. Q. During compaction the soil is completely saturated. R. In consolidation, volume reduction is due to expulsion of pore water from voids. S. Compaction is almost an instantaneous phenomenon. Identify the correct statement(s), and choose correct answer.', 'P and Q only', 'R and S only', 'P, Q and R only', 'P, Q and S only', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c39bc91d-4a88-42c6-b1f7-ae4fc2b0dba1', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'Match the items under List 1 (Test/Equipment) with those under List 2 (Purpose of test for soil). Use codes in list for matching. P. Hydrometer Q. Ring and Water replacement method R. Sand bath method S. Casagrande''s apparatus', 'P-4,Q-3,R-1,S-2', 'P-3,Q-4,R-2,S-1', 'P-2,Q-3,R-1,S-4', 'P-4,Q-1,R-2,S-3', 2, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c39bc91d-4a88-42c6-b1f7-ae4fc2b0dba1', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'What is the correct sequence of occurrence of the Atterberg limits : Shrinkage limit (SL) Liquid limit(LL) , Plastic limit (PL) when the moisture content of a clayey soil reduced from a large value to a lower value gradually. Use the symbols for answering.', 'SL, PL, LL', 'LL, SL, PL', 'PL, SL, LL', 'LL, PL, SL', 4, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c39bc91d-4a88-42c6-b1f7-ae4fc2b0dba1', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The saturated unit weight of a soil sample is estimated as 20.64 kN/m³. If the unit weight of water is 10 kN/m³, estimate the submerged unit weight of soil (in kN/m³ units)?', '10.64', '20.64', '30.64', '2.064', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c39bc91d-4a88-42c6-b1f7-ae4fc2b0dba1', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'The following statements (P, Q) pertaining to a soil mass are given. P. A high value of dry unit weight indicates a more compact soil. Q. When the soil is at its liquid limit, its liquidity index is zero. Identify the correct statement(s) and choose the correct option.', 'P only', 'Q only', 'Both P and Q', 'Neither P nor Q', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c39bc91d-4a88-42c6-b1f7-ae4fc2b0dba1', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'If q_u is the ultimate bearing capacity of a soil, then the net safe bearing capacity q_ns is given by : (Notations : F - factor of safety, D_f - depth of foundation, γ - unit weight of soil)', '(q_u - γD_f)/F', '(q_u + γD_f)/F', 'q_u - γD_f/F', 'q_u + γD_f/F', 1, NULL, 'medium'),
('e33338c9-740c-48c4-914b-2cca3e9c1668', 'c39bc91d-4a88-42c6-b1f7-ae4fc2b0dba1', 2023, 'Paper-II', 'As per IS classification Fine sand size particle are of diameter ranging from :', '4.75 mm to 20 mm', '4.75 mm to 2 mm', '2 mm to 0.425 mm', '0.425 mm to 0.075 mm', 4, NULL, 'medium');
